[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat java.base/java.util.regex.Pattern$[0m[1;35mBranch.match[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPattern.jav[0m[1;92ma:4734[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat java.base/java.util.regex.Pattern$[0m[1;35mCharProperty.match[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPattern.jav[0m[1;92ma:3931[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mTRUNCATED[0m[1;39m][0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA stack overflow vulnerability has been detected in the Java regex pattern matching[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation. The issue manifests as a `java.lang.StackOverflowError` wrapped in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma `FuzzerSecurityIssueLow` exception, occurring during regex pattern matching [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations within the `java.util.regex.Pattern` class. The stack trace shows a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepetitive cycle of method calls involving `Pattern$[0m[1;35mBranch.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Pattern$[0m[1;35mGroupHead.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `Pattern$[0m[1;35mLoop.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `Pattern$[0m[1;35mGroupTail.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Pattern$[0m[1;35mBranchConn.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and `Pattern$[0m[1;35mCharProperty.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, indicating an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munbounded recursive execution.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Overview[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue is a stack overflow error that occurs during regex pattern matching in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJava's standard library. The error is classified as a low-severity security issue [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby the fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueLow`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuggesting it represents a potential denial-of-service vulnerability rather than a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical security flaw. The fuzzer indicates that the issue can be reproduced with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma stack size of 921k [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`-Xss921k`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is a **Regular Expression Denial of Service [0m[1;39m([0m[39mReDoS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** vulnerability [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanifesting as a stack overflow. The issue occurs when a regex pattern causes [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcessive recursive backtracking during the matching process, eventually exhausting[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe call stack.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Repetitive Call Pattern**: The stack trace shows a highly repetitive cycle of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe following method calls:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Pattern$[0m[1;35mBranchConn.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m4698[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Pattern$[0m[1;35mCharProperty.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m3931[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Pattern$[0m[1;35mBranch.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m4734[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Pattern$[0m[1;35mGroupHead.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m4789[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Pattern$[0m[1;35mLoop.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m4898[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Pattern$[0m[1;35mGroupTail.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m4820[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Recursive Nature**: The pattern suggests unbounded recursion where the regex [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mengine enters a loop that repeatedly attempts to match nested groups, branches, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops without reaching a termination condition.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Pattern Components Involved**: The stack trace indicates the regex pattern [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlikely contains:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Branches [0m[1;39m([0m[39malternation using `|`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Groups [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcapturing or non-capturing[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Loops/quantifiers [0m[1;39m([0m[39msuch as `*`, `+`, `?`, or `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mn,m[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Character properties or character classes[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Severity Classification**: The issue is marked as [0m[32m"Low"[0m[39m severity, but stack [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow errors can still lead to application crashes and denial of service [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditions.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Investigation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a comprehensive understanding of this issue, the following areas should be [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvestigated:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Input Pattern Analysis**: Examine the specific regex pattern that triggers [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis behavior. The pattern likely contains nested quantifiers, complex [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malternations, or overlapping repetitions that cause catastrophic backtracking.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Test Harness or Entry Point**: Identify where regex patterns are being [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompiled and matched in the codebase. This includes:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Code that accepts user-provided regex patterns[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Code that constructs regex patterns dynamically[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Areas where patterns are used for validation, parsing, or text processing[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Pattern Validation**: Review any existing validation or sanitization [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmechanisms for regex patterns to determine if they adequately prevent problematic [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatterns.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Regex Pattern Usage**: Survey all locations in the codebase where [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mMatcher.matches[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or related methods are used, [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparticularly where input patterns come from external sources.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Recursion Depth Handling**: Investigate if there are any existing mechanisms [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto limit recursion depth or timeout long-running regex operations.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Similar Patterns**: Check for other regex patterns in the codebase that might [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexhibit similar structural characteristics [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnested quantifiers, complex [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malternations, overlapping patterns[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that could be vulnerable to the same issue.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Java Version Compatibility**: Verify which version of Java is being used, as [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdifferent versions may have different regex engine implementations and [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moptimizations.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of Code Snippets in Relation to Evaluation Report[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Core Insights from Code Analysis[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Root Cause Identified**: The vulnerability is in `ChangeSet.java` at line [0m[1;36m103[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the `[0m[1;35maddDeletion[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   final Pattern pattern = [0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[39msource + [0m[32m"/.*"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The code directly concatenates user-provided directory names with regex syntax [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout escaping regex metacharacters.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Attack Vector**: When `[0m[1;35mdeleteDir[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString dirName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called with a malicious [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory name containing nested quantifiers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[32m"[0m[32m([0m[32m([0m[32ma+[0m[32m)[0m[32m+[0m[32m)[0m[32m+"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the resulting [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern causes catastrophic backtracking during matching operations, leading to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack overflow.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Reference Implementation Found**: The codebase already contains the correct [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern in `ZipSplitReadOnlySeekableByteChannel.java` at line [0m[1;36m104[0m[39m:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   final Pattern pattern = [0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileBaseName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m".[0m[32m[[0m[32mzZ[0m[32m][0m[32m[[0m[32m0-9[0m[32m][0m[32m+"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This demonstrates the proper use of `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to escape user input.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Critical Logic to Preserve**: [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35maddDeletion[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method serves two purposes: adding deletion changes and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpre-filtering to remove conflicting ADD operations[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The regex pattern is only used for the [0m[1;33mDELETE[0m[39m_DIR operation type [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m113[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The actual deletion in `ChangeSetPerformer` uses safe `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The optimization logic must be preserved while making it safe[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Previous Patches**: This is the initial fix attempt, so no previous patches[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneed to be reapplied.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Comprehensive Fix Strategy[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Apply [0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to Escape User Input[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: `src/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/changes/ChangeSet.java`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m103[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Current Code**:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinal Pattern pattern = [0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[39msource + [0m[32m"/.*"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Fixed Code**:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinal Pattern pattern = [0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[39msource[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[32m"/.*"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation Details**:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrap the `source` variable with `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before concatenating with the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregex suffix [0m[32m"/.*"[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This treats the directory name as a literal string, preventing any regex [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetacharacters from being interpreted as regex syntax[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The [0m[32m"/.*"[0m[39m suffix remains unquoted so it continues to function as a regex pattern [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatching anything under the directory[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Verify No Additional Changes Required[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Import Verification**: [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `java.util.regex.Pattern` is already imported at line [0m[1;36m25[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No additional imports are needed since `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is a static method of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe already-imported Pattern class[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**API Surface**: [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No changes to public methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mdelete[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35mdeleteDir[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;35madd[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fix is entirely internal to the private `[0m[1;35maddDeletion[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintains backward compatibility[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Minimal Change**: Single-line modification that adds only `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrapper around the user input[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Follows Existing Pattern**: Matches the approach already used successfully in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipSplitReadOnlySeekableByteChannel.java`[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **No API Changes**: Internal fix that doesn't affect public method signatures or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Standard Java Solution**: Uses Java's built-in `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifically designed for this purpose[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Logic[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Functionality Maintained**: The pattern still matches entries under the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecified directory[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For normal directory names: `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"bla"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[32m"/.*"[0m[39m` becomes [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"\\Qbla\\E/.*"[0m[39m` which matches [0m[32m"bla/..."[0m[39m correctly[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For names with metacharacters: `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"test+"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` becomes [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"\\Qtest+\\E"[0m[39m` treating [0m[32m"+"[0m[39m as literal[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Optimization Logic Intact**: The pre-filtering of conflicting ADD operations [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinues to work[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Test Compatibility**: All existing tests use simple directory names and will [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to pass[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Issues[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Prevents ReDoS**: By escaping regex metacharacters, nested quantifiers like [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m[32m([0m[32m([0m[32ma+[0m[32m)[0m[32m+[0m[32m)[0m[32m+"[0m[39m are treated as literal strings[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Eliminates Stack Overflow**: No catastrophic backtracking can occur when the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern is matched[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Security Improvement**: Closes the denial-of-service vulnerability while [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaintaining functionality[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect**: [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m expected. The change makes the code safer without altering [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mits behavior for legitimate use cases.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Testing Considerations**:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Existing tests with normal directory names [0m[1;39m([0m[32m"bla"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"META-INF"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will pass [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fix should be validated with directory names containing regex metacharacters [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto ensure they're now handled safely[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Performance impact is negligible since `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is a simple string [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mescaping operation[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase already demonstrates this exact pattern in [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipSplitReadOnlySeekableByteChannel.java`:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinal Pattern pattern = [0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileBaseName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m".[0m[32m[[0m[32mzZ[0m[32m][0m[32m[[0m[32m0-9[0m[32m][0m[32m+"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis confirms that:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The approach is already validated within the project[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. It's the established pattern for handling user input in regex compilation[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. It's proven to work correctly in production code[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Conclusion[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix strategy applies a single-line change using `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to escape [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muser-provided directory names before regex compilation. This follows the [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mestablished pattern in the codebase, prevents the ReDoS vulnerability, eliminates [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe stack overflow issue, and maintains full backward compatibility with existing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality. The fix requires no new dependencies, no API changes, and no [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodifications to test code or harness code.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a `StackOverflowError` originating from Java's regex pattern [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatching operations, specifically within the `java.util.regex.Pattern` class [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Branch.match`, `GroupHead.match`, `Loop.match`, `GroupTail.match`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BranchConn.match`, and `CharProperty.match`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A patch was attempted that added [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to escape special regex characters in a filename pattern used in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ChangeSet.java`. However, after applying the patch, the same `StackOverflowError` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersists with nearly identical stack traces, indicating the patch did not resolve [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe underlying issue.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue presents a `StackOverflowError` wrapped in a [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueLow` exception. The stack trace shows a repeating cycle of [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod calls within Java's regex engine:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Pattern$[0m[1;35mBranch.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Pattern$[0m[1;35mGroupHead.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Pattern$[0m[1;35mLoop.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Pattern$[0m[1;35mGroupTail.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Pattern$[0m[1;35mBranchConn.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `Pattern$[0m[1;35mCharProperty.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis repetitive pattern indicates that the regex engine is entering into deep [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecursive calls, eventually exhausting the stack space. The error message suggests [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39musing `-Xss921k` to reproduce the issue, which indicates the stack overflow occurs [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a specific stack size configuration.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The error is classified as a security issue [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlow severity[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m by the fuzzer[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The stack overflow occurs during regex pattern matching operations[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The recursive nature of the calls suggests a problematic regex pattern that [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcauses catastrophic backtracking or excessive recursion[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The issue is reproducible with specific input that triggers this behavior[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Details[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch was applied to [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/changes/ChangeSet.java` at line [0m[1;36m103[0m[39m:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Original code:**[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinal Pattern pattern = [0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[39msource + [0m[32m"/.*"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Patched code:**[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinal Pattern pattern = [0m[1;35mPattern.compile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[39msource[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[32m"/.*"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe modification wraps the `source` variable with `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which escapes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many special regex metacharacters in the source string. This approach aims to [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent user-controlled input from being interpreted as regex syntax, which could [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotentially create problematic patterns.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mContext of the change:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code is within a method that processes delete changes[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `source` variable comes from `[0m[1;35mdeleteChange.getTargetFileName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The pattern is used to match filenames that start with the source path followed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby a forward slash and any characters [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95m.[0m[39m*`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The pattern is later used to filter changes in an iterator loop[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result Analysis[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the `StackOverflowError` continues to occur with a very [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilar stack trace. The key observations from the post-patch behavior:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The same recursive cycle of regex engine methods is still present[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The stack trace structure remains virtually identical to the original issue[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The error still originates from `Pattern$[0m[1;35mLoop.match[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and involves the same [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequence of internal regex engine calls[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The patch did not eliminate or significantly reduce the stack overflow[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis indicates that:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `[0m[1;35mPattern.quote[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` fix addresses potential regex injection but does not solve [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe stack overflow issue[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The problematic pattern may be in the `[0m[35m/[0m[95m.[0m[39m*` portion that was not modified[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- There may be additional locations in the codebase with similar regex patterns [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcausing the issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The input triggering the fuzzer may be exploiting the `[0m[35m/[0m[95m.[0m[39m*` pattern rather than [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecial characters in the `source` variable[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Further Investigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **The regex pattern `[0m[35m/[0m[95m.[0m[39m*` itself**: This pattern, when used with certain inputs [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor in combination with other patterns, can lead to catastrophic backtracking. The [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`.*` quantifier is greedy and can cause exponential time complexity in certain [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatching scenarios.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Input characteristics**: Understanding what specific input the fuzzer [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgenerates that triggers this stack overflow would help identify whether the issue [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis with:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Very long filenames[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Deeply nested path structures[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Specific character sequences that cause backtracking[0m                           [2m                [0m
